				 for the most part i think your right, but i know from lots and lots of experiance that asking people nicely for items works very well. Someone was even going to give me crushes tunic(no joke) for free just because i asked for it. I was given bronze and cast iron rapires and a fs short sword for free. I also got a cutthroat insignia ring. Usually when somebody says &quot;first lvl 1 druid to poke me gets a free gift&quot;, ill go and poke them and act surprised when they say &quot;your not a druid&quot;. In this case i was given 2 scrolls that sold for about 1pp each at a merchant. I dont care if im a begger, at least im not dead or low on cash. <BR>
